  "prompt": "What is production line?",
  "response": "A production line is a manufacturing system where a product is assembled or processed in a step-by-step manner, typically on a conveyor belt or similar setup. Each worker or machine along the line performs a specific task, adding or modifying components until the final product is complete. This method, pioneered by Henry Ford in the early 20th century, increases efficiency, reduces production time, and allows for mass production of goods.",
